    <bioghist encodinganalog="545$a">
      <head>Biographical Information
</head>
      <p>Jeff Trollinger is a member of the pastoral care team of St. Michael Catholic Church in Glen Allen, Virginia.  Trollinger represents the <title xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" render="doublequote" xlink:href="">We are Family</title> portion of the team, which focuses on ministry to Gay and Lesbian Catholics, their families and their friends.  He was the vice chair of the Sexual Minorities Commission of the Catholic Church for the years 2000-2002 and the chair of the commission from 2002 until 2004, during which time he collected current events in papers and magazines dealing with gay rights concerns and gay representation in religion.  The Commission on Sexual Minorities was the first attempt by a Catholic diocese to reach out to homosexual parishioners when it was established in 1977 in Richmond, Virginia by Bishop Walter Sullivan.  While it was not instantly accepted by many in the church, there were more than forty commissions like it twenty years later.  It was disbanded in 2004 when Bishop Francis DiLorenzo was appointed to Richmond.</p>
      <p>Jeff Trollinger was also a member of Other Voices: The Richmond Lesbian and Gay Chorus, and was made president of the steering committee in 1999.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520$a">
      <head>Scope and Content
</head>
      <p>The Jeff Trollinger Papers consist of information from the Sexual Minorities Commission including minutes, correspondence, membership files, publications, and a handbook entitled National Association of Catholic Diocesan Lesbian and Gay Ministries (NACDLGM).  There is also a large section of papers relating to the Other Voices Chorus.  These have minutes, correspondence, membership files, a board member handbook, state incorporation papers, sheet music, and information from the Gay and Lesbian Association (GALA) of Choruses Conference. There is also a videotape. The bulk of the collection consists of original and photocopied scrapbooks kept by Mr. Trollinger that consist of news articles relating to the gay community.</p>
    </scopecontent>
    <arrangement encodinganalog="351">
      <head>Arrangement
</head>
      <p>Materials in the collection are in alphabetical order within each series, with the exception of the scrapbooks which are kept in their original order.  Photocopies of the scrapbooks are sorted by date.</p>
      <p>There are three series in this collection.  Series I is the Sexual Minorities Commission, 1975, 1980, 1990-2005, undated.  Series II is Other Voices Chorus, 1993-1999, undated.  Scrapbooks are series III, dated 1990-2004.  Photocopies of the scrapbooks are filed first with originals following.  The originals have the complete listing of all headlines.</p>
    </arrangement>
